description:
Southern Storm



Aired on 04/23/2008, Narrated by Jonathan Aris



On 4 April 1977, Southern Airways Flight 242, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9-31, on a flight from Huntsville, Alabama to Atlanta, Georgia, flies through a severe thunderstorm and is hit by large hailstones. Both engines of the DC-9-31 fail and the aircraft makes an emergency landing on a highway in New Hope, Paulding County, Georgia. However, it collides with a gas station and explodes, killing 62 people on board and eight on the ground; two more die later of injuries sustained during the crash.
